It is with heavy heart that I must inform everyone that as of now, the development of EverGuild software will not continue.  This is due partly to the massive scale that the project has turned out to be, and the difficulty of one person to complete it.  In addition, to the fact that another guild software already exists which I see no way that EverGuild could possibly compete against.<BR><BR>

For those looking for guild software, you might wish to check out a software called GuildBoss, which is at http://www.guildboss.com.  Plesae note that I have never used this, and in no way am officially endorcing this software, but from looking at the screen shots, and features list which is already has, it looks alot better than I was planning for EverGuild to become.<BR><BR>

What does this mean for the immedate future?  EverGuild will remain on launcher for another week or two until it is removed.  I will focus more on EverMon now adding in some of the feature requests that have been building up over the last month, and possibly take on another EverQuest project in the future, if one presents itself.<BR><BR>

<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Wednesday, July 14th, 1999</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>11:28 - New Bug and Feature Tracking Added!</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>

Check out the New <a href=eg_bug.asp>Bug Tracking</a> and the new <a href=eg_feature.asp>
Feature Tracking</a> pages that have been set up for EverGuild.  You can find
them by clicking on the 'support' menu option under EverGuild to the left
of the page.<br><br>

<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Thursday, July 8th, 1999</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>10:47 - Nilwad officially added to EverGuild team.</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>

Although Nilwad has already been assisting with EverGuild support and operations
in the background now for some time, today he is officially being given the
title of <b>Head of the EverGuild Network Support Team</b>!  You will now
also find his contact information in the EverGuild Support Page.<br><Br>

<B>- <A HREF='mailto:bryonq@hydracomp.com'>Zackron</A></B></BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=5 COLS=1 WIDTH='80%' BACKGROUND='barback.jpg'><TR><TD><B><FONT COLOR='#FFFFCC' SIZE=+2>Friday, July 2nd, 1999</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>15:21 - More EverGuild changes coming next week...</FONT></B><BLOCKQUOTE>

First, a special Thank You! to everyone who has provided feedback in the
form of both bug reports and feature suggestions this week.  With updates
and changes needing to be made to the Launcher software, as well as to the
entire hydracomp.com website, there were not many public updates to EverGuild,
save a few bug and crashing fixes.  However, There are some major changes
planned for Next week, including the addition of the Message Board System,
and the Calaendar and Event System, as well as hopefully the addition of
an 'Off-Line' mode that will allow users to access EverGuild messages,
chatting, etc. even when the Stat Server is not avalible.<br><Br>

